Two people were arrested in connection with two separate killings in Oukasie near Brits, North West police said on Monday. Brigadier Sabata Mokgwabone said the two suspects allegedly committed the murders on New Year s Day in Oukasie Phase 3. In the first incident a man died at a local hospital after allegedly being stabbed at a local tavern. The police were told by the victim s father that the suspect, aged 19, allegedly stabbed his son with a knife. He informed the police that the incident occurred at one of the local taverns in Oukasie location. Mokgwabone said the suspect was later traced and arrested. Investigation into the matter continues. In the second incident, also on Sunday, a 32-year-old man was stabbed in the neck. The man and the suspect, a woman aged 21, had an argument that led to the latter fatally stabbing the man with unknown object, Mokgwabone said. The victim was certified dead on the scene and the suspect was arrested. Investigation into the matter continues. The two were expected to appear in the Brits Magistrate s Court on Tuesday. African News Agency (ANA)